reviewText: I am very picky about what comes into my home, but Spaced Invaders is a very silly family friendly imagination movie. I first saw it years ago (possibly on the Disney Channel). The aliens are obviously sily characters and will not scare your children. There is no sexual referencing, but a few cuss words (maybe like "damn", or "what the hell?") but it is to few it is able to be ignored. Although it is timed to be around Halloween, trick-or-treating and costumes (family friendly, not tacky). I recommend this movie for a fun family laugh session any time of year.
summary: Spaced Invaders: A must see family movie
